 interfaces-first composable-boundaries — is a gate alongside correctness not a nice-to-have. Audits apply the beauty filter as primary lens. Workspace beauty extends beyond code to capture discipline (avoid duplicate intent records) report retention (avoid proliferation without retirement) and substrate cleanliness (no hand-written code where schema can drive).|] High Minimum Zero [beauty design])) (7d4x ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [Newly-designed components must actually drive the live system end to end — the three engines, trait-defined ordering, typestate mail, origin route are the real execution drivers, not dead scaffolding beside an older code path. Verify in implementation that every designed component is on the live path.] High Minimum Zero [implementation prove-not-pretend engine])) (a2t4 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [Horizon and its cluster-data are minimal on two axes. At the semantic boundary Horizon expresses only WHAT the psyche-as-cluster-user wants — simple typed facts, never HOW; Nix consumes them and owns all composition and decision-complexity. At the type-count level reuse the input type as the output type rather than parallel in/out types. Upstream principle for the Horizon rewrite.] High Minimum Zero [horizon nix])) (izsf ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [Psyche design decisions apply to the WHOLE design unless explicitly scoped, not just the local prompt example. When absorbing any psyche design correction, ask 'where else does this rule apply structurally?' before stopping at the surface where the example was given.] High Minimum Zero [psyche-intent design])) (lrfa ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [Value lean, efficient design and do not fear breaking things. Breakage belongs in development, not production; breaking freely in development is what development is for. Lean means no duplication and no boilerplate, not the fewest lines.] High Minimum Zero [design])) (w85v ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Correction [|Crate and module names must honestly describe what the thing is; a name that abbreviates a capability the thing lacks (naming a crate 'auth' when it is not an authentication library, the signal-persona-auth case) is wrong.|] High Minimum Zero [naming signal-persona-auth])) (izib ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Decision [Domain subdomains are mandatory all the way to a leaf, so a domain value is always complete. DomainScope is not Domain with optional payloads; it is a separate generated prefix language over the same recursive domain tree, a ScopeOf construct, where stopping early is the prefix semantics rather than optional subdomain data. Every scope segment is a typed enum variant and the notation stays clean with no Some or None exposed; the generator owns the internal representation] Medium VeryHigh Zero [domain-scope domain schema])) (06l6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [|Most workspace logic is MATCHES between two domains: domain A enum times domain B enum, the logic being the match-matrix outcome per cell. Cells with no defined behavior return a typed error or help (Unavailable etc) — the error surface IS part of the trait surface. Engine operations expose these tree-to-tree and enum-to-enum matching surfaces.|] Medium Minimum Zero [match-matrix engine design])) (4ivz ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Correction [Use plain English for schema root terminology: the authored schema root should be described as a struct with fields named input and output, not as abstract surfaces unless that term is specifically needed. Avoid invented vocabulary when ordinary field/struct language says the thing directly.] Medium Minimum Zero [schema naming])) (cam8 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [Design analysis targets the ideal: for each thing, work out the best, most correct, future-oriented, reusable